{"id": 51968, "date": "2024-06-16T06:00:00", "date_gmt": "2024-06-16T13:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "https://estreetshuffle.com/?p=51968"}, "modified": "2024-06-16T06:33:17", "modified_gmt": "2024-06-16T13:33:17", "slug": "cover-me-turn-on-your-love-light", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2024/06/16/cover-me-turn-on-your-love-light/", "title": {"rendered": "Cover Me: Turn On Your Love Light"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>If you ask me which classic R&amp;B songs deserve to turn up on Bruce&#8217;s next album of soul covers, &#8220;Turn On Your Love Light&#8221; would be near the top of my list.</p>\n<p>I mean&nbsp;<em>come on</em>: How can anyone in E Street Nation listen to Bobby &#8220;Blue&#8221; Bland&#8217;s classic 1961 hit and not hear its influence on Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band?</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Bobby Blue Bland   Turn On Your Love Light\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/StdN_CiCNS4?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>With a killer horn riff, lovelorn vocals, desperate begging, and that sax solo taking us <em>a little bit higher</em>, &#8220;Turn on Your Love Light&#8221; would have been just as much at home on the Born to Run Tour as on World Tour 2024.</p>\n<p>Heck, you can even hear its influence on the Seeger Sessions Band!</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"You Can Look (But You Better Not Touch) - Bruce Springsteen (26-04-2006 Convention Hall,Asbury Park)\" width=\"758\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/I6gdWeKJ4hE?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>So it&#8217;s absolutely mystifying that Springsteen has yet to perform it on the E Street stage.</p>\n<p>Even if somehow Bruce hadn&#8217;t latched on to Bland&#8217;s original (which made it to #2 on the Billboard R&amp;B chart and #28 on the Hot 100), it seems like virtually all of his musical influences were covering it in the sixties. From Van Morrison&#8230;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Turn on Your Love Light\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/PM4dRIvb4_I?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>&#8230;to Mitch Ryder&#8230;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Let Your Love Light Shine\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/RQaPju2Pik0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>&#8230;to Jerry Lee Lewis and more.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Turn On Your Love Light\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/U-VVYPRIhrQ?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>And then of course, there are the epic Grateful Dead jams (some of which even included a familiar guest saxophonist).</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"The Grateful Dead - Turn On Your Lovelight w/ Clearence Clemons - 06-21-1989 - Shoreline\" width=\"758\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/37W3zdVfmgc?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>So why no Springsteen concert performances in the last half-century? Beats the heck out of me. The closest we&#8217;ve come is a handful of hat-tips during the band intros on the Rising Tour.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Bruce Springsteen : Mary&#039;s Place (with a snippet of Bobby &#039;Blue&#039; Bland &#039;s TURN ON YOUR LOVE LIGHT)\" width=\"758\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2IHntRdm9B8?start=456&#038;feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>Maybe it has something to do with the few times he <em>did </em>perform it, some 53 years ago during a trio (at least) of club gigs at the Jersey Shore.</p>\n<p>It was during Bruce&#8217;s Steel Mill era, and the band was, shall we say, loose. (I&#8217;m guessing more than a few drinks had been consumed.) And while there are plenty of classic rock songs that would have been well-suited for a guitar-heavy Steel Mill jam treatment, &#8220;Turn On Your Love Light&#8221; isn&#8217;t one of them.</p>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\">document.createElement('audio');</script><![endif]-->\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-51968-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Turn-On-Your-Love-Light.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Turn-On-Your-Love-Light.mp3\">https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Turn-On-Your-Love-Light.mp3</a></audio>\n<p>Yikes. I could understand shying away from a song after a performance like that.</p>\n<p>But come on, Bruce. Enough time has passed. You&#8217;ve got the horns, and you&#8217;ve got Bland&#8217;s ability to turn on a dime from crooner to preacher. It&#8217;s time to give &#8220;Turn On Your Love Light&#8221; a proper outing.</p>\n<p>Let it shine!</p>\n<p><strong>Turn On Your Love Light<br />\nFirst performed:&nbsp;</strong>November 27, 1970 (Asbury Park, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:&nbsp;</strong>January 22, 1971 (Asbury Park, NJ)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Set the wayback machine for 1971 to hear Bruce Springsteen and Steel Mill cover one of the seminal R&#038;B classics.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 51969, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [4], "tags": [3593, 2902, 33, 1698], "class_list": ["post-51968", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "tag-bobby-bland", "tag-grateful-dead", "tag-steel-mill", "tag-van-morri